column2: What is the status of these participants in the community or organization?
column11: How much self-confidence do these participants have?
column20: How much free time do these participants have?
column28: What is the education level of these participants?
column37: Do these participants have physical limitations that will impact their participation?
column45: Do these participants have emotional impairments that will impact their participation (such as mental illness or traumatic stress)?
column53: For these participants, how important is performing well (with "high marks")?
column61: For these participants, how important is conforming (to what is "normal" or expected)?
column69: For these participants, how important is self-promotion (competing with others)?
column77: For these participants, how important is speaking out (having a say, venting, sounding off)?
column85: How motivated are these participants to participate in the project?
column94: How are these participants likely to feel about the project?
column101: How do these participants feel about you?
column108: How do these participants feel about the idea of collecting stories?
column115: What experiences have these participants had with the project's topic?
column124: How private do these participants consider the topic to be?
column131: How hard will it be for these participants to articulate their feelings about the topic?
column138: How long of a time period do you need these participants to look back on?
column147: How much experience do you have facilitating PNI projects?
column153: How much help will you have carrying out this project?
column159: How many technological resources will you have for carrying out this project?
